{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a63417cc3fb48d65aaa", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 150, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eba2"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "615d92eade3d91842a5cf7d0", "title": "JEE Main 2012 (26 May Online)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "A beam of light consisting of red, green and blue colours is incident on a right-angled prism on face $A B$. The refractive indices of the material for the above red, green and blue colours are $1.39,1.44$ and $1.47$ respectively. A person looking on surface $A C$ of the prism will see\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/jee_main/pQydq4gkXDU_k_2uKv7S5j_1OLjRr8Y4CbD2WYBjec0.original.fullsize.png\"><br>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "Z8k2H", "text": "\nno light\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pNO3w", "text": "\ngreen and blue colours\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "RXAhB", "text": "\nred and green colours\n", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "6mRwP", "text": "\nred colour only", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "For light to come out through face 'AC', total internal reflection must not take place.\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\text { i.e., } \\theta < c \\Rightarrow \\sin \\theta < \\sin c \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow \\sin \\theta < \\frac{1}{\\mu}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nor $\\quad \\mu < \\frac{1}{\\sin \\theta} \\Rightarrow \\mu < \\frac{1}{\\sin 45^{\\circ}}$\n$$\n\\Rightarrow \\mu < \\sqrt{2} \\Rightarrow \\mu < 1.414\n$$", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId